{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"Thank you for putting up these pictures of my colleagues over here."},{"time":4000,"text":"(Laughter) We'll be talking about them."},{"time":9000,"text":"Now, I'm going try an experiment. I don't do experiments, normally. I'm a theorist."},{"time":14000,"text":"But I'm going see what happens if I press this button."},{"time":18000,"text":"Sure enough. OK. I used to work in this field of elementary particles."},{"time":23000,"text":"What happens to matter if you chop it up very fine?"},{"time":27000,"text":"What is it made of?"},{"time":29000,"text":"And the laws of these particles are valid throughout the universe,"},{"time":34000,"text":"and they're very much connected with the history of the universe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":37000,"text":"We know a lot about four forces. There must be a lot more,"},{"time":40000,"text":"but those are at very, very small distances,"},{"time":42000,"text":"and we haven't really interacted with them very much yet."},{"time":45000,"text":"The main thing I want to talk about is this:"},{"time":49000,"text":"that we have this remarkable experience in this field of fundamental physics"},{"time":53000,"text":"that beauty is a very successful criterion for choosing the right theory."},{"time":60000,"text":"And why on earth could that be so?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":65000,"text":"Well, here's an example from my own experience."},{"time":68000,"text":"It's fairly dramatic, actually, to have this happen."},{"time":73000,"text":"Three or four of us, in 1957,"},{"time":76000,"text":"put forward a partially complete theory of one of these forces, this weak force."},{"time":81000,"text":"And it was in disagreement with seven -- seven, count them, seven experiments."},{"time":87000,"text":"Experiments were all wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90000,"text":"And we published before knowing that,"},{"time":92000,"text":"because we figured it was so beautiful, it's gotta be right!"},{"time":95000,"text":"The experiments had to be wrong, and they were."},{"time":98000,"text":"Now our friend over there, Albert Einstein,"},{"time":101000,"text":"used to pay very little attention when people said,"},{"time":105000,"text":"\"You know, there's a man with an experiment that seems to disagree with special relativity."},{"time":110000,"text":"DC Miller. What about that?\" And he would say, \"Aw, that'll go away.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"Now, why does stuff like that work? That's the question."},{"time":122000,"text":"Now, yeah, what do we mean by beautiful? That's one thing."},{"time":127000,"text":"I'll try to make that clear -- partially clear."},{"time":130000,"text":"Why should it work, and is this something to do with human beings?"},{"time":135000,"text":"I'll let you in on the answer to the last one that I offer,"},{"time":138000,"text":"and that is, it has nothing to do with human beings."},{"time":140000,"text":"Somewhere in some other planet, orbiting some very distant star,"},{"time":145000,"text":"maybe in a another galaxy,"},{"time":147000,"text":"there could well be entities that are at least as intelligent as we are,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and are interested in science. It's not impossible; I think there probably are lots."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156000,"text":"Very likely, none is close enough to interact with us."},{"time":159000,"text":"But they could be out there, very easily."},{"time":164000,"text":"And suppose they have, you know, very different sensory apparatus, and so on."},{"time":170000,"text":"They have seven tentacles, and they have 14 little funny-looking compound eyes,"},{"time":175000,"text":"and a brain shaped like a pretzel."},{"time":179000,"text":"Would they really have different laws?"},{"time":182000,"text":"There are lots of people who believe that, and I think it is utter baloney."},{"time":186000,"text":"I think there are laws out there,"},{"time":188000,"text":"and we of course don't understand them at any given time very well"},{"time":194000,"text":"-- but we try. And we try to get closer and closer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"And someday, we may actually figure out the fundamental unified theory"},{"time":201000,"text":"of the particles and forces, what I call the \"fundamental law.\""},{"time":206000,"text":"We may not even be terribly far from it."},{"time":208000,"text":"But even if we don't run across it in our lifetimes,"},{"time":211000,"text":"we can still think there is one out there,"},{"time":214000,"text":"and we're just trying to get closer and closer to it."},{"time":216000,"text":"I think that's the main point to be made."},{"time":219000,"text":"We express these things mathematically."},{"time":222000,"text":"And when the mathematics is very simple --"},{"time":224000,"text":"when in terms of some mathematical notation,"},{"time":228000,"text":"you can write the theory in a very brief space, without a lot of complication --"},{"time":234000,"text":"that's essentially what we mean by beauty or elegance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":238000,"text":"Here's what I was saying about the laws. They're really there."},{"time":244000,"text":"Newton certainly believed that."},{"time":246000,"text":"And he said, here, \"It is the business of natural philosophy to find out those laws.\""},{"time":256000,"text":"The basic law, let's say -- here's an assumption."},{"time":259000,"text":"The assumption is that the basic law really takes the form"},{"time":262000,"text":"of a unified theory of all the particles."},{"time":265000,"text":"Now, some people call that a theory of everything."},{"time":268000,"text":"That's wrong because the theory is quantum mechanical."},{"time":273000,"text":"And I won't go into a lot of stuff about quantum mechanics and what it's like, and so on."},{"time":277000,"text":"You've heard a lot of wrong things about it anyway. (Laughter)"},{"time":282000,"text":"There are even movies about it with a lot of wrong stuff."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"But the main thing here is that it predicts probabilities."},{"time":290000,"text":"Now, sometimes those probabilities are near certainties."},{"time":293000,"text":"And in a lot of familiar cases, they of course are."},{"time":296000,"text":"But other times they're not, and you have only probabilities for different outcomes."},{"time":302000,"text":"So what that means is that the history of the universe is not determined just by the fundamental law."},{"time":308000,"text":"It's the fundamental law and this incredibly long series of accidents,"},{"time":313000,"text":"or chance outcomes, that are there in addition."}]},{"cues":[{"time":318000,"text":"And the fundamental theory doesn't include those chance outcomes; they are in addition."},{"time":324000,"text":"So it's not a theory of everything. And in fact, a huge amount of the information"},{"time":328000,"text":"in the universe around us comes from those accidents,"},{"time":332000,"text":"and not just from the fundamental laws."},{"time":335000,"text":"Now, it's often said that getting closer and closer"},{"time":343000,"text":"to the fundamental laws by examining phenomena at low energies, and then higher energies,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and then higher energies, or short distances, and then shorter distances,"},{"time":351000,"text":"and then still shorter distances, and so on, is like peeling the skin of an onion."},{"time":355000,"text":"And we keep doing that,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and build more powerful machines, accelerators for particles."},{"time":361000,"text":"We look deeper and deeper into the structure of particles,"},{"time":366000,"text":"and in that way we get probably closer and closer to this fundamental law."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"Now, what happens is that as we do that, as we peel these skins of the onion,"},{"time":379000,"text":"and we get closer and closer to the underlying law,"},{"time":382000,"text":"we see that each skin has something in common with the previous one,"},{"time":387000,"text":"and with the next one. We write them out mathematically,"},{"time":391000,"text":"and we see they use very similar mathematics."},{"time":394000,"text":"They require very similar mathematics."},{"time":397000,"text":"That is absolutely remarkable, and that is a central feature"},{"time":401000,"text":"of what I'm trying to say today."},{"time":406000,"text":"Newton called it -- that's Newton, by the way -- that one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409000,"text":"This one is Albert Einstein. Hi, Al! And anyway,"},{"time":416000,"text":"he said, \"nature conformable to herself\" -- personifying nature as a female."},{"time":423000,"text":"And so what happens is that the new phenomena,"},{"time":428000,"text":"the new skins, the inner skins of the slightly smaller skins of the onion"},{"time":434000,"text":"that we get to, resemble the slightly larger ones."},{"time":438000,"text":"And the kind of mathematics that we had for the previous skin"},{"time":444000,"text":"is almost the same as what we need for the next skin."},{"time":448000,"text":"And that's why the equations look so simple."},{"time":452000,"text":"Because they use mathematics we already have."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455000,"text":"A trivial example is this: Newton found the law of gravity,"},{"time":460000,"text":"which goes like one over the square of the distance between the things gravitated."},{"time":465000,"text":"Coulomb, in France, found the same law for electric charges."},{"time":470000,"text":"Here's an example of this similarity."},{"time":472000,"text":"You look at gravity, you see a certain law."},{"time":475000,"text":"Then you look at electricity. Sure enough. The same rule."},{"time":478000,"text":"It's a very simple example."},{"time":480000,"text":"There are lots of more sophisticated examples."},{"time":484000,"text":"Symmetry is very important in this discussion."},{"time":486000,"text":"You know what it means. A circle, for example,"},{"time":489000,"text":"is symmetric under rotations about the center of the circle."},{"time":493000,"text":"You rotate around the center of the circle, the circle remains unchanged."},{"time":498000,"text":"You take a sphere, in three dimensions, you rotate around the center of the sphere,"},{"time":501000,"text":"and all those rotations leave the sphere alone."},{"time":505000,"text":"They are symmetries of the sphere."},{"time":506000,"text":"So we say, in general, that there's a symmetry"},{"time":510000,"text":"under certain operations if those operations leave the phenomenon,"},{"time":514000,"text":"or its description, unchanged."}]},{"cues":[{"time":517000,"text":"Maxwell's equations are of course symmetrical"},{"time":520000,"text":"under rotations of all of space."},{"time":522000,"text":"Doesn't matter if we turn the whole of space around by some angle,"},{"time":526000,"text":"it doesn't leave the -- doesn't change the phenomenon of electricity or magnetism."},{"time":530000,"text":"There's a new notation in the 19th century that expressed this,"},{"time":534000,"text":"and if you use that notation, the equations get a lot simpler."},{"time":538000,"text":"Then Einstein, with his special theory of relativity,"},{"time":541000,"text":"looked at a whole set of symmetries of Maxwell's equations,"},{"time":544000,"text":"which are called special relativity."},{"time":547000,"text":"And those symmetries, then, make the equations even shorter, and even prettier, therefore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":552000,"text":"Let's look. You don't have to know what these things mean, doesn't make any difference."},{"time":555000,"text":"But you can just look at the form. (Laughter) You can look at the form."},{"time":559000,"text":"You see above, at the top, a long list"},{"time":561000,"text":"of equations with three components for the three directions of space: x, y and z."},{"time":567000,"text":"Then, using vector analysis, you use rotational symmetry, and you get this next set."},{"time":573000,"text":"Then you use the symmetry of special relativity and you get an even simpler set"},{"time":577000,"text":"down here, showing that symmetry exhibits better and better."},{"time":581000,"text":"The more and more symmetry you have, the better you exhibit the simplicity and elegance of the theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587000,"text":"The last two, the first equation says that electric charges and currents"},{"time":591000,"text":"give rise to all the electric and magnetic fields."},{"time":595000,"text":"The next -- second -- equation says that there is no magnetism other than that."},{"time":600000,"text":"The only magnetism comes from electric charges and currents."},{"time":603000,"text":"Someday we may find some slight hole in that argument."},{"time":608000,"text":"But for the moment, that's the case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"Now, here is a very exciting development that many people have not heard of."},{"time":616000,"text":"They should have heard of it, but it's a little tricky to explain in technical detail,"},{"time":621000,"text":"so I won't do it. I'll just mention it. (Laughter)"},{"time":624000,"text":"But Chen Ning Yang, called by us \"Frank\" Yang -- (Laughter)"},{"time":634000,"text":"-- and Bob Mills put forward, 50 years ago,"},{"time":638000,"text":"this generalization of Maxwell's equations, with a new symmetry."},{"time":642000,"text":"A whole new symmetry."},{"time":644000,"text":"Mathematics very similar, but there was a whole new symmetry."},{"time":647000,"text":"They hoped that this would contribute somehow to particle physics"},{"time":652000,"text":"-- didn't. It didn't, by itself, contribute to particle physics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":656000,"text":"But then some of us generalized it further. And then it did!"},{"time":661000,"text":"And it gave a very beautiful description of the strong force and of the weak force."},{"time":666000,"text":"So here we say, again, what we said before:"},{"time":669000,"text":"that each skin of the onion shows a similarity to the adjoining skins."},{"time":673000,"text":"So the mathematics for the adjoining skins is very similar to what we need for the new one."},{"time":678000,"text":"And therefore it looks beautiful"},{"time":680000,"text":"because we already know how to write it in a lovely, concise way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684000,"text":"So here are the themes. We believe there is a unified theory underlying all the regularities."},{"time":693000,"text":"Steps toward unification exhibit the simplicity."},{"time":697000,"text":"Symmetry exhibits the simplicity."},{"time":699000,"text":"And then there is self-similarity across the scales -- in other words,"},{"time":703000,"text":"from one skin of the onion to another one."},{"time":705000,"text":"Proximate self-similarity. And that accounts for this phenomenon."},{"time":710000,"text":"That will account for why beauty is a successful criterion for selecting the right theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"Here's what Newton himself said:"},{"time":718000,"text":"\"Nature is very consonant and conformable to her self.\""},{"time":722000,"text":"One thing he was thinking of is something that most of us take for granted today,"},{"time":726000,"text":"but in his day it wasn't taken for granted."},{"time":729000,"text":"There's the story, which is not absolutely certain to be right, but a lot of people told it."},{"time":735000,"text":"Four sources told it. That when they had the plague in Cambridge,"},{"time":739000,"text":"and he went down to his mother's farm -- because the university was closed --"},{"time":743000,"text":"he saw an apple fall from a tree, or on his head or something."},{"time":747000,"text":"And he realized suddenly that the force that drew the apple down to the earth"},{"time":751000,"text":"could be the same as the force regulating the motions of the planets and the moon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":757000,"text":"That was a big unification for those days, although today we take it for granted."},{"time":762000,"text":"It's the same theory of gravity."},{"time":766000,"text":"So he said that this principle of nature, consonance:"},{"time":771000,"text":"\"This principle of nature being very remote from the conceptions of philosophers,"},{"time":776000,"text":"I forbore to describe it in that book,"},{"time":779000,"text":"lest I should be accounted an extravagant freak ... \""},{"time":783000,"text":"That's what we all have to watch out for, (Laughter) especially at this meeting."},{"time":788000,"text":"\" ... and so prejudice my readers against all those things which were the main design of the book.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":793000,"text":"Now, who today would claim that as a mere conceit of the human mind?"},{"time":797000,"text":"That the force that causes the apple to fall to the ground"},{"time":801000,"text":"is the same force that causes the planets and the moon to move around,"},{"time":804000,"text":"and so on? Everybody knows that. It's a property of gravitation."},{"time":809000,"text":"It's not something in the human mind. The human mind can, of course, appreciate it"},{"time":813000,"text":"and enjoy it, use it, but it's not -- it doesn't stem from the human mind."},{"time":818000,"text":"It stems from the character of gravity."},{"time":820000,"text":"And that's true of all the things we're talking about."},{"time":822000,"text":"They are properties of the fundamental law."},{"time":824000,"text":"The fundamental law is such that the different skins of the onion resemble one another,"},{"time":830000,"text":"and therefore the math for one skin allows you to express beautifully and simply"},{"time":834000,"text":"the phenomenon of the next skin."}]},{"cues":[{"time":837000,"text":"I say here that Newton did a lot of things that year:"},{"time":840000,"text":"gravity, the laws of motion, the calculus, white light composed of all the colors of the rainbow."},{"time":846000,"text":"And he could have written quite an essay on \"What I Did Over My Summer Vacation.\""},{"time":852000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":856000,"text":"So we don't have to assume these principles as separate metaphysical postulates."},{"time":866000,"text":"They follow from the fundamental theory."},{"time":872000,"text":"They are what we call emergent properties."},{"time":874000,"text":"You don't need -- you don't need something more to get something more."},{"time":881000,"text":"That's what emergence means."}]},{"cues":[{"time":883000,"text":"Life can emerge from physics and chemistry, plus a lot of accidents."},{"time":892000,"text":"The human mind can arise from neurobiology and a lot of accidents,"},{"time":897000,"text":"the way the chemical bond arises from physics and certain accidents."},{"time":904000,"text":"It doesn't diminish the importance of these subjects"},{"time":908000,"text":"to know that they follow from more fundamental things, plus accidents."},{"time":914000,"text":"That's a general rule, and it's critically important to realize that."},{"time":919000,"text":"You don't need something more in order to get something more."},{"time":923000,"text":"People keep asking that when they read my book, \"The Quark and the Jaguar,\""},{"time":927000,"text":"and they say, \"Isn't there something more beyond what you have there?\""},{"time":931000,"text":"Presumably, they mean something supernatural."},{"time":935000,"text":"Anyway, there isn't. (Laughter)"},{"time":937000,"text":"You don't need something more to explain something more."},{"time":942000,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]}]}